 The Osun State Police Command, on Friday, confirmed the arrest of two suspects in connection with the killings of Hassan Adedeji, a graduate of the Federal Polytechnic, Ede, and a commercial motorcyclist. Hassan, a fresh graduate of Banking and Finance at Ede Polytechnic, was reportedly killed by unknown gunmen on Wednesday night. The aggrieved students of the institution took to the streets in protest against the incident on Thursday. It was learnt that rampaging hoodlums killed three other persons in what was suspected to be a rival cult clash. The Police Public Relations Officer, Osun State Command, SP Yemisi Opalola, confirmed that two persons had been arrested in connection with the recent killings in the town. According to her, the prime suspect, named Rasheed Okolu, is still on the run. She said that “The prime suspect, Rasheed Okolu, killed a man at his den. We discovered the dead body at his den, chained and killed. “Police are everywhere in the Ede community to ensure that he is arrested and brought to justice. Our men are on the ground tackling cultists in that axis. The situation is under control.” 